\[ 7 \text{ weeks} \times 20 \text{ hours/week} = 140 \text{ hours} \]

Since Cathy took Chris's shifts, she also worked 140 hours. Therefore, the total number of hours Cathy worked is:
\[ 8 \text{ weeks} \times 20 \text{ hours/week} = 160 \text{ hours} \]

So, the number of hours Cathy worked during the 2 months is:
\[ \boxed{160} \] 
